# Switching to unstable releases
# because stable release quit compiling and installing correctly.

    stable 3.00
  unstable 3.01a03 3.01a02
   require acl
  optional syslinux     '' '' to create bootable CDROMs and DVDs
  optional zisofs-tools '' '' to create ISO9660s enabled with transparent compression
  category disk/cd
 attribute console
case $VERSION in
*a*)source ftp://ftp.berlios.de/pub/cdrecord/alpha/cdrtools-$VERSION.tar.gz ;;
  *)source ftp://ftp.berlios.de/pub/cdrecord/cdrtools-$VERSION.tar.gz ;;
esac
      info home  http://cdrecord.berlios.de/old/private/cdrecord.html
      info docs  http://cdrecord.berlios.de/old/private/man/cdrecord/index.html
  estimate 3400
      desc 'utility for burning CDs with a CD-R/CD-RW recorder
Cdrecord supports CD recorders from many different vendors;
all SCSI-3/mmc and ATAPI/mmc compliant drives should also work.
Supported features include IDE/ATAPI, parallel-port,
and SCSI drives, audio CDs, data CDs, and mixed CDs,
full multi-session support, CD-RWs (rewritable), TAO,
DAO and human-readable error messages.
Cdrecord includes remote SCSI support and
can access local or remote CD-writers.

To burn on IDE cdrecords a typical dev parameter might be
dev=ATAPI:/dev/hdf
Running cdrecord using ide-scsi emulation is no longer recommended.'

build(){
# sed -i "66i#include <linux/compiler.h>
#         66itypedef unsigned char u8;" libscg/scsi-linux-sg.c
 make &&
 make install INS_BASE=$DESTDIR/usr
}
